      <layout class="QVBoxLayout" name="verticalLayout_2">
       <item>
        <widget class="QLabel" name="labelDescription">
         <property name="sizePolicy">
          <sizepolicy hsizetype="Minimum" vsizetype="Preferred">
           <horstretch>0</horstretch>
           <verstretch>0</verstretch>
          </sizepolicy>
         </property>
         <property name="text">
          <string>&lt;p&gt;Select the appropriate volumes for preop and post volumes as well as the STL for the planned PSI. Then click on the button to prepare the scene by applying naming and coloring conventions as described in the documentation. If (parts of) this process cannot be performed automatically carefully study the console output to determine what you have to do manually.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Finally a rough alignment of the volumes by centering them on their bounding boxes is performed&lt;/p&gt;</string>
         </property>
         <property name="wordWrap">
          <bool>true</bool>
         </property>
        </widget>
       </item>
