          <string>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Important:&lt;/b&gt; This step is only necessary if the STL-files of the plan do not align with the preop CT (e.g. because the planner changed the coordinate system)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To achieve alignment the preop-CT is segmentat and convertet to a surface model. The planning STL of the bone is then registered to the preop model&lt;/p&gt;</string>
         </property>
