     <widget class="QWidget" name="pageSegmentPSI">
      <property name="geometry">
       <rect>
        <x>0</x>
        <y>0</y>
        <width>684</width>
        <height>301</height>
       </rect>
      </property>
      <attribute name="label">
       <string>3. Segment intraop PSI</string>
      </attribute>
      <layout class="QVBoxLayout" name="verticalLayout_4">
       <item>
        <widget class="QLabel" name="label_2">
         <property name="text">
          <string>&lt;p&gt;When you click on the button a new segmentation for the postopeative psi position is created and the programm switches to the &lt;i&gt;segment editor module&lt;/i&gt;. Here you should use the &lt;i&gt;Threshold&lt;/i&gt; tool to roughly segment the psi by its density. Then use the &lt;i&gt;Scissors&lt;/i&gt; tool to remove any excess voxcels that to not belong to the psi, but to the surrounding bone. It is not necessary to create a perfect segmentation, but rather the correct outlines of the PSI for later registration with the planned STL model&lt;/p&gt;</string>
         </property>
         <property name="wordWrap">
          <bool>true</bool>
         </property>
        </widget>
       </item>
       <item>
